                  <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  <msItem>
                     <p> 
                        <persName>
                           <forename>Peter</forename> de <surname>Shipton</surname>, son of <persName>
                              <forename>Stephen</forename>, the priest, of <placeName role="priest" key="place_109412">Orton</placeName>
                           </persName>
                        </persName>,
               grants to the <orgName key="org_109067">church and canons of Oseney</orgName>, the donation which
               <persName>
                           <forename>Ralph</forename> de <surname>Melkesham</surname>
                        </persName> made to them of one virgate
               of land in <placeName key="place_109257">Donestiwe</placeName>, which was of the lordship of
               <persName>
                           <forename>Stephen</forename> 
                           <surname>Runcin</surname>
                        </persName>, with a messuage
               near the house of <persName>
                           <forename>Wimund</forename> de <surname>Donestiwe</surname>
                        </persName>, which
               land the said Ralph deraigned by a certain assise before 
               <persName>
                           <forename>Mart.</forename> de <surname>Pateshall</surname>
                        </persName> and others, 
               the King's justices at <placeName key="place_105449">Oxford</placeName> against the said
               <persName nymRef="Runtin">
                           <forename>Peter</forename>
                        </persName> and 
               <persName>
                           <forename>Roger</forename> 
                           <surname>Runcin</surname>
                        </persName> and
               <persName>
                           <forename>Henry</forename> 
                           <surname>Ruf[fus]</surname>
                        </persName>; paying annually one 
               pair of gloves of the value of one halfpenny. 
               (<origDate notBefore="1225" notAfter="1230" precision="low">c. 1225-30</origDate>.) 
               Henry Ruffus is a witness.
               . </p>
